  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustaining Life Saving Health, Nutrition and WASH services through Integrated Emergency Response Teams (IERTs) for conflict and drought affected populations in Hiran and Lower Juba</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is in line with cluster strategic objectives by providing integrated live saving health, nutrition and WASH services for the cluster priority districts in Hiran (Beletweyn, Mataban) and Lower Jubba (Kismayo). The project will contribute to improving equitable access to quality life-saving curative and preventative health and nutrition services through the support of static health facilities and in some places mobile outreach. There will be twenty integrated health and nutrition sites in the two districts (8 in Beletweyn, 7 in Mataban and 5 in Kismayo). The integrated health and nutrition teams will provide outpatient consultations, routine immunizations, maternal healthcare, disease surveillance and health promotion. As well as systematic identi&#xFB01;cation, referral and treatment of acutely malnourished cases by providing integrated nutrition services to OTS, TSFP and Stabilization centers. The provision of OTP services for those with SAM and the referral and treatment of SAM cases with medical complications to the nearest stabilization centre. Micronutrient supplementation, promotion of IYCF practices, promoting the adoption of good hygiene and sanitation practices will be done, providing treatment for all age groups, both male and female. The health and nutrition interventions will improve early identification and prevention of malnutrition, and access to primary health care, and therefore reduce excess morbidity and mortality. The WASH component in health and nutrition will also improve good hygiene practices, more equitable and better access to sustainable water points for drinking and handwashing with soap, and to basic sanitation services in these facilities and surrounding communities. Hygiene and sanitation support and promotion will be provided in an integrated approach in the health and nutrition sites, there will also be outreach nutrition, hygiene and health promotion within the community and in schools, this will also empower Children to be agents of change for hygiene promotion.</narrative>
  </description>
